[Crim. No. 3234. In Bank. May 15, 1929.] In the Matter of the Application of A. EMORY WISHON for Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Murray Bourne and Thelen & Marrin for Petitioner.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and Charles A. Wetmore, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

Upon the authority of the Matter of the Application of Battelle for Writ of Habeas Corpus, filed May 14, 1929, ante, p. 227 [277 Pac. 725], the order for commitment herein is vacated and the petitioner discharged.
